etymologies: Middle English: from Latin quinquefolium, from quinque ‘five’ + folium ‘leaf’

definitions: a widely distributed herbaceous plant of the rose family, with compound leaves of five leaflets and five-petaled yellow flowers.

notes.text: Genus Potentilla, family Rosaceae: numerous species, including the small-flowered creeping common cinquefoil (P. simplex) and the larger-flowered erect rough-fruited cinquefoil (P. recta)

shortDefinitions: widely distributed herbaceous plant of rose family, with compound leaves of five leaflets and five-petalled yellow flowers

definitions: an ornamental design of five lobes arranged in a circle, e.g. in architectural tracery or heraldry.
shortDefinitions: ornamental design of five lobes arranged in circle
